@NODE Installation
In order to install Cruncher, you first need to copy at least one of the
cruncher libraries supplied to your LIBS: drawer. This can easily be done
by using the supplied InstallLibs script. You then just drag the main
Cruncher program wherever you want to put it.
@ENDNODE

@NODE Future
Possible future additions to Cruncher
=====================================
 * Support any other crunchers. If you know of any you would like me to
   support, then please could you write to me, preferably with details of
   how I can crunch the files.
 * Batch processing a number of files.
 * Support crunching using a password.
 * Anything you suggest (within reason naturally).
@ENDNODE

@NODE crunchers "Supported Crunchers"
At the moment XPKGuide supports the following crunchers:

	P-Compress		You don't need any special library
				installed to be able to use the
				P-Compress cruncher.
	CrunchMania		To be able to crunch files using the
				CrunchMania cruncher, you need to have
				the CrM.library version 4 or higher
				installed.
	lh.library		Cruncher produces files crunched using
				the lh.library which are compatible with
				the LhEncode and LhDecode programs which
				were supplied with the main lh.library
				package. This is on Fish Disk 436.
	PowerPacker		To crunch files using the PowerPacker
				compressors you will need to have the
				powerpacker.library version 35 or
				higher installed.
	Any XPK sublibrary	You need to have the xpkmaster.library
				installed in order to be able to crunch
				any XPK files. You also need at least one
				cruncher library.

I have only used standard compression formats, I haven't dreamed up any
new variations.
@ENDNODE

@NODE arexx "ARexx Commands"
Crunchers ARexx port basename is CRUNCHER. This means that the first copy
of Cruncher which you run will have the port name CRUNCHER.01, the second
will have the port name CRUNCHER.02, etc. up to CRUNCHER.99.

Here is a list of the supported ARexx commands:

	@{"ABOUT      " link rexx_about}
	@{"CRMHUFF    " link rexx_crmhuff}
	@{"CRMNORMAL  " link rexx_crmnormal}
	@{"CRMNOSAMPLE" link rexx_crmnosample}
	@{"CRMSAMPLE  " link rexx_crmsample}
	@{"CRUNCH     " link rexx_crunch}
	@{"CRUNCHMANIA" link rexx_crunchmania}
	@{"DEST       " link rexx_dest}
	@{"EFFICIENCY " link rexx_efficiency}
	@{"LHLIB      " link rexx_lhlib}
	@{"PCOMPRESS  " link rexx_pcompress}
	@{"POWERPACKER" link rexx_powerpacker}
	@{"SOURCE     " link rexx_source}
	@{"QUIT       " link rexx_quit}
	@{"XPK        " link rexx_xpk}
@ENDNODE

@NODE rexx_about "ARexx Command: ABOUT"
This option brings up the about requester and waits for the user to close
it before continuing.
@ENDNODE

@NODE rexx_crmhuff "ARexx Command: CRMHUFF"
This command tells Cruncher to use the CrunchMania LZH crunch routine
instead of the normal one if you try to crunch using the CrunchMania
compressor. The LZH crunch routine produces smaller files than the normal
cruncher, but is also slower at decrunching.

See also: @{"CRMNORMAL" link rexx_crmnormal}, @{"CRMNOSAMPLE" link rexx_crmnosample}, @{"CRMSAMPLE" link rexx_crmsample}, @{"CRUNCHMANIA" link rexx_crunchmania}
@ENDNODE

@NODE rexx_crmnormal "ARexx Command: CRMNORMAL"
This command tells Cruncher to use the normal CrunchMania cruncher instead
of the LZH cruncher if you try to crunch using the CrunchMania cruncher.
The normal CrunchMania cruncher can be decrunched faster than the LZH
cruncher, but also produces larger files than the LZH cruncher.

See also: @{"CRMHUFF" link rexx_crmhuff}, @{"CRMNOSAMPLE" link rexx_crmnosample}, @{"CRMSAMPLE" link rexx_crmsample}, @{"CRUNCHMANIA" link rexx_crunchmania}
@ENDNODE

@NODE rexx_crmnosample "ARexx Command: CRMNOSAMPLE"
This command tells Cruncher to not use CrunchManias sound sample
crunching mode when crunching any files with the CrunchMania cruncher.
This gives better results when not crunching samples than when the sample
cruncher mode is active. This mode can be used with either the normal
CrunchMania cruncher or the LZH CrunchMania cruncher.

See also @{"CRMHUFF" link rexx_crmhuff}, @{"CRMNORMAL" link rexx_crmnormal}, @{"CRMSAMPLE" link rexx_crmsample}, @{"CRUNCHMANIA" link rexx_crunchmania}
@ENDNODE

@NODE rexx_crmsample "ARexx Command: CRMSAMPLE"
This command tells Cruncher to use CrunchManias special sound sample
crunching mode when crunching any files with the CrunchMania cruncher.
This gives better results when you are crunching any files which contain a
lot of samples than if you crunching the files without the sample mode
active. This mode can be used with either the normal CrunchMania cruncher
or the LZH CrunchMania cruncher.

See also @{"CRMHUFF" link rexx_crmhuff}, @{"CRMNORMAL" link rexx_crmnormal}, @{"CRMNOSAMPLE" link rexx_crmnosample}, @{"CRUNCHMANIA" link rexx_crunchmania}
@ENDNODE

@NODE rexx_crunch "ARexx Command: CRUNCH"
This command does the same as the user pressing the Crunch gadget in the
main window. The only difference is that where the CrunchMania preferences
window normally comes up if you have the CrunchMania cruncher selected,
the window isn't opened, but instead the current settings are used. The
current settings can be altered using the @{"CRMHUFF" link rexx_crmhuff], @{"CRMNORMAL" link rexx_crmnormal}, @{"CRMNOSAMPLE" link rexx_crmnosample}
and @{"CRMSAMPLE" link rexx_crmsample} ARexx commands.
@ENDNODE

@NODE rexx_crunchmania "ARexx Command: CRUNCHMANIA"
This command tells Cruncher to select the CrunchMania compressor as the
current cruncher if it is available. If the CrM.library isn't available
then this command returns 10 in RC.

See also: @{"CRMHUFF" link rexx_crmhuff}, @{"CRMNORMAL" link rexx_crmnormal}, @{"CRMNOSAMPLE" link rexx_crmnosample}, @{"CRMSAMPLE" link rexx_crmsample}, @{"LHLIB" link rexx_lhlib},
          @{"POWERPACKER" link rexx_powerpacker}, @{"PCOMPRESS" link rexx_pcompress}, @{"XPK" link rexx_xpk}
@ENDNODE

@NODE rexx_dest "ARexx Command: DEST"
This command allows you to specify what file you want Cruncher to write
the crunched packed file to. You can also specify a directory, in this
case the file will keep its current name but will be put in the
destination directory.
If you do give any arguments then that will be put in the filename gadget
automatically. If you are giving a filename then you will probably need to
put quotes around it as in the following example:

DEST 'Ram Disk:A File'

This will put the string "Ram Disk:A File" in the filename gadget without
including the quotes.

See also: @{"SOURCE" link rexx_source}
@ENDNODE

@NODE rexx_efficiency "ARexx Command: EFFICIENCY"
This command allows you to select the efficiency of the compression, it
goes from 0 up to 100 with 100 being the best compression and usually the
slowest. Here is how the efficiency number relates to PowerPackers
compression modes:

	From	To	Mode
	=========================
	0	20	Fast
	21	40	Mediocre
	41	60	Good
	61	80	Very good
	81	100	Best

The CrunchMania and LhLib crunchers don't support different efficiencies.
Some XPK crunchers support different efficiencies while others don't so if
you use this command, if the selected cruncher supports it, the crunching
mode will be changed otherwise the command will just be ignored.
@ENDNODE

@NODE rexx_lhlib "ARexx Command: LHLIB"
This command tells Cruncher to select the lh.library compressor as the
current cruncher if it is available. If it isn't available then the
command returns 10 in RC.

See also: @{"CRUNCHMANIA" link rexx_crunchmania}, @{"POWERPACKER" link rexx_powerpacker}, @{"PCOMPRESS" link rexx_pcompress}, @{"XPK" link rexx_xpk}
@ENDNODE

@NODE rexx_pcompress
This command tells Cruncher to select the P-Compress compressor as the
current cruncher.

See also: @{"CRUNCHMANIA" link rexx_crunchmania}, @{"LHLIB" link rexx_lhlib}, @{"POWERPACKER" link rexx_powerpacker}
@ENDNODE

@NODE rexx_powerpacker "ARexx Command: POWERPACKER"
This command tells Cruncher to select the PowerPacker compressor as the
current cruncher if it is available. If the powerpacker.library isn't
available then the command returns 10 in RC.

See also: @{"CRUNCHMANIA" link rexx_crunchmania}, @{"LHLIB" link rexx_lhlib}, @{"PCOMPESS" link rexx_pcompress}, @{"XPK" link rexx_xpk}
@ENDNODE

@NODE rexx_source "ARexx Command: SOURCE"
This command allows you to specify which file you want Cruncher to crunch.
If you don't specify any arguments then a file requester will be brought
up to allow the user to select a file.
If you do give any arguments then that will be put in the filename gadget
automatically. If you are giving a filename then you will probably need to
put quotes around it as in the following example:

SOURCE 'Ram Disk:A File'

This will put the string "Ram Disk:A File" in the filename gadget without
including the quotes.

See also: @{"DEST" link rexx_dest}
@ENDNODE

@NODE rexx_quit "ARexx Command: QUIT"
This command tells Cruncher to quit. No requester is brought up to ask
the user if they are sure they want to quit.
@ENDNODE

@NODE rexx_xpk "ARexx Command: XPK"
This command allows you to select an XPK cruncher. You have to supply the
name of the XPK cruncher after the XPK, e.g. "XPK NUKE".
The case of the cruncher name doesn't matter. If you don't have the XPK
cruncher installed then this command will return 10 in RC.

See also: @{"CRUNCHMANIA" link rexx_crunchmania}, @{"LHLIB" link rexx_lhlib}, @{"PCOMPRESS" link rexx_pcompress}, @{"POWERPACKER" link rexx_pcompress}
@ENDNODE
